During the 2021-2022 academic year, Biola University handed out 15 bachelor's degrees in computer science. This is a decrease of 21% over the previous year when 19 degrees were handed out.
There were 5,296 students enrolled at Biola University in 2023. In 2023, 1,260 degrees were awarded across all undergraduate and graduate programs.
In the 2020-2021 academic year, 19 students received a bachelor's degree in computer science from Biola.
There are 3,596 undergraduate students at Biola, with 3,289 being full-time and 307 being part-time. There are also 1,955 graduate students at the school.
